wiki.content: “What Was I Made For?" by Billie Eilish is a haunting and emotional ballad, written for the 2023 film Barbie. It delves into themes of identity, purpose, and existential questioning, reflecting the struggles of trying to find meaning in an ever-changing world. With Eilish's soft, breathy vocals, the song is minimalistic yet deeply resonant, capturing feelings of melancholy and introspection. Its poignant lyrics, like "I used to float, now I just fall down", reflect a sense of loss and confusion, while asking what one’s true purpose is, especially when grappling with emotional turmoil. The song continued Billie Eilish’s award-winning streak, earning her both the Grammy for Song of the Year and Best Song Written for Visual Media, as well as her second Oscar for Best Original Song. These prestigious honors highlight the song’s emotional depth and resonance, cementing Eilish’s place as one of the most influential artists of her generation. Read more on Last.fm.
